# Trade Integrity Dashboard — Sub-Agent Orchestration

You are coordinating the upgrade of a Trade Integrity Dashboard for NSE index futures (BANKNIFTY, NIFTY). The upgrade is broken into 7 specialized sub-agents that MUST be executed in dependency order.

## System Context
```
STACK:  Python backend (fetch_and_analyze.py) → enriched_trades.json → React frontend (App.jsx)
DATA:   5-min OHLC candles, 20-period EMA, 9:15-15:30 IST, cached in candle_cache/
DEPS:   Python: numpy, pandas, stdlib only | React: Tailwind CSS, SVG/Canvas only, no charting libs
```

## Sub-Agent Execution Order (STRICT)

When asked to upgrade the Trade Integrity Dashboard, execute these sub-agents in this exact order. Each must complete and validate before the next begins.

### Phase 1 — Python Backend (sequential, each depends on previous)

1. **@core-logic-fixer** → Fixes 5 bugs in fetch_and_analyze.py (EMA slope, leg reset, trendline, market phase, signal bar)
   - Validate: `python fetch_and_analyze.py` runs. New flags: marketPhase, emaSlope, emaSlopeClassification, trendlineIntact

2. **@indicator-builder** → Adds 12 new detection functions to fetch_and_analyze.py
   - Validate: All new flag fields from schema-contract appear in output JSON

3. **@scoring-engine** → Rewrites scoring with decomposition, quality classification, mistake tags
   - Validate: Every trade has scoreDecomposition, tradeQuality, mistakeTag, thesis, reality

4. **@session-builder** → Builds shared sessions object for chart data export
   - Validate: sessions keys match all sessionKey values. Each session has ~75 candles + ema array

### Phase 2 — React Frontend (5 + 6 can run in parallel, 7 depends on both)

5. **@card-ui** → Card badges, heatmap clicks, anti-portfolio toggle, visual upgrades in App.jsx
   - Validate: `npm run dev` in dashboard/ — no console errors

6. **@detail-view** → Full-session candlestick modal, annotations, replay slider in App.jsx
   - Validate: Modal opens on card click, renders ~75 bars, annotations toggle

7. **@anti-mistake** → Learning system: quality matrix, win rate chart, discipline timeline in App.jsx
   - Validate: Win rate brackets correct, quality matrix sums to total trades

## Validation Protocol (After Each Sub-Agent)
- Schema compliance: new fields match [schema-contract](mdc:schema-contract.mdc)
- No regressions: existing fields unchanged
- File scope: agent only modified its designated files
- No new dependencies: no pip install or npm install
- Runnable: python/npm runs without errors

## When to Spawn Sub-Agents
- If asked to "upgrade the dashboard" or "run the full upgrade" → run all 7 in order
- If asked to "fix the Python backend" → run phases 1-4
- If asked to "upgrade the frontend" → run phases 5-7
- If asked about a specific feature (e.g., "add market phase detection") → spawn only the matching sub-agent
